 both glandular and squamous components.&nbsp; The hyperplastic component often accounting for no less than 70% of the tumor (Haqqani &amp; Fox 1976).  Endometrial hyperplasia, especially atypical hyperplasia is a well-established precursor to the most common type of endometrial cancer, endometrioid adenocarcinoma (Boardman et al., 2023; Hecht et al., 2005; Huvila et al., 2021).", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 14:56:53 +0000 2026"}